@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit Worker Autoscaling with KEDA

' Queue backlog drives the worker count. One more pod per 3 queued, floor 1.

skinparam shadowing false

queue "job.requests\n(backlog = lag)" as topic
component "KEDA\nreads consumer group lag" as keda
component "HPA" as hpa
node "python-worker pods\n1 to 10" as pods

topic --> keda : how many messages are waiting
keda --> hpa : desired = ceil(lag / 3)
hpa --> pods : scale up or down
pods --> topic : consume and commit, lag drops

note bottom of keda
  floor 1, ceiling 10. scales back to 1
  about 30 seconds after the backlog clears.
end note

note bottom of pods
  one consumer per partition. the topic has 12,
  so more pods means more parallel work.
end note

@enduml
